        {
          "type": "assistant",
          "text": "Here's what happens when an error occurs, based on the rescue block at lines 39-45:\n\n**The flow:**\n1. Bot transitions to `'error'` status (line 40)\n2. Error is logged (line 41)\n3. The error is re-raised (wrapped in `Grid::Initializer::Error` if it wasn't already)\n\n**The problem — partial state is left behind.** Depending on *where* it fails, you get different debris:\n\n| Failure point | What's already persisted |\n|---|---|\n| `fetch_and_store_instrument_info!` | Nothing — clean |\n| `fetch_current_price!` | Instrument info saved on bot |\n| `calculate_grid` | + `quantity_per_level` saved |\n| `ensure_base_balance!` | + possible market buy already executed on exchange (irreversible) |\n| `persist_grid_levels` | + some GridLevel records in DB |\n| `place_orders_in_batches` | + some orders placed on exchange + Order/GridLevel records |\n| `register_dcp!` / `seed_redis` | Bot is `running` but Redis/DCP may be incomplete |\n\nThe biggest concern is **lines 31-33**: if `persist_grid_levels` succeeds and `place_orders_in_batches` partially succeeds, you have orders live on Bybit but the bot is in `'error'` status. There's no cleanup that cancels those orphaned exchange orders.\n\nAlso note that `register_dcp!` (line 36) and `seed_redis` (line 37) run *after* `transition_to!('running')` — if they fail, the bot is already `'running'` in DB, then gets set back to `'error'`. But DCP failure is soft (just a warning log, line 213), so only `seed_redis` could cause this.\n\nWould you like me to plan a fix? The main options are:\n1. **Rollback approach** — cancel any placed orders on Bybit in the rescue block\n2. **Resume approach** — make initialization idempotent so it can be retried from where it left off\n3. **Transaction approach** — wrap DB writes in a transaction (doesn't help with exchange-side state though)",
