            "prompt": "Design a rollback mechanism for Grid::Initializer when errors occur during bot initialization.\n\n## Current Problem\n\nGrid::Initializer (`app/services/grid/initializer.rb`) has no rollback. When it fails mid-initialization:\n- Exchange orders already placed remain live on Bybit\n- GridLevel and Order DB records persist in partial state\n- Bot transitions to 'error' status\n- When user retries from 'error', the controller (`app/controllers/api/v1/bots_controller.rb` lines 100-102) does `@bot.orders.delete_all` and `@bot.grid_levels.delete_all` WITHOUT cancelling exchange orders first\n\n## Current Initialization Flow (lines 26-45)\n```ruby\ndef execute_initialization!\n  fetch_and_store_instrument_info!       # API call, saves to bot\n  current_price = fetch_current_price!   # API call\n  levels, classification, qty = calculate_grid(current_price)  # Pure computation + bot update\n\n  ensure_base_balance!(classification, qty)  # May place MARKET BUY on exchange (irreversible)\n  grid_levels = persist_grid_levels(levels, classification)  # Creates GridLevel records\n  place_orders_in_batches(grid_levels, classification, qty)  # Places LIMIT orders on exchange + creates Order records\n\n  transition_to!('running')\n  register_dcp!          # Best-effort, already handles failure gracefully\n  seed_redis             # Seeds Redis state\n  kick_off_reconciliation\nrescue StandardError => e\n  transition_to!('error') unless @bot.status == 'error'\n  Rails.logger.error(\"[Initializer] Bot #{@bot.id} failed: #{e.message}\")\n  raise Error, e.message unless e.is_a?(Error)\n  raise\nend\n```\n\n## Available Tools\n\n### Bybit REST Client (`app/services/bybit/rest_client.rb`)\n- `cancel_all_orders(symbol:, emergency: false)` — bulk cancel all open orders for a symbol\n- `cancel_order(symbol:, order_id:)` — cancel single order\n- `get_open_orders(symbol:)` — query open orders\n\n### Existing Cleanup Patterns\n\n**Grid::Stopper** (`app/services/grid/stopp